In Australia, the album achieved Gold status, representing 35,000 units shipped. Japan, a notoriously robust market for physical music, also awarded it Gold certification for 100,000 units. New Zealand saw the album reach Platinum status, signifying 15,000 units. The [United Kingdom](/United_Kingdom), [Fatboy Slim](/Fatboy_Slim)'s home turf, demonstrated the strongest performance, with the album earning Platinum certification for 300,000 units. In the [United States](/United_States), while not officially certified, the album recorded sales of 278,000 units, a respectable figure for an electronic music album in a market often dominated by other genres. These numbers, of course, are merely indicators of market penetration, not necessarily artistic merit. But then, who truly cares about artistic merit when the ledgers balance?

